What are XPath Axes?

XPath axes XPath ke special keywords hote hain jo DOM (Document Object Model) me element ke relationship ko define karte hain.

Inka use parent, child, sibling, ancestor elements locate karne ke liye hota hai.

Simple words me:

XPath axes allow us to navigate through different nodes in the DOM relative to the current element.

Common XPath Axes in Selenium
1️⃣ Parent Axis

Current element ke parent element ko locate karta hai.

Example:

//input[@id='username']/parent::div

➡️ Username input ke parent div ko locate karega.

2️⃣ Child Axis

Current element ke child elements locate karta hai.

//div[@class='form']/child::input

➡️ Div ke andar jo input hai usko locate karega.

3️⃣ Ancestor Axis

Current element ke sabhi parent levels locate karta hai.

//input[@id='username']/ancestor::form

➡️ Input ke upar jo form element hai usko locate karega.

4️⃣ Following Axis

Current element ke baad ke elements locate karta hai.

//label[text()='Username']/following::input

➡️ Label ke baad jo input hai usko locate karega.

5️⃣ Following-Sibling Axis

Current element ke same level ke next sibling elements locate karta hai.

//label[text()='Username']/following-sibling::input

➡️ Label ke next input field ko locate karega.

6️⃣ Preceding Axis

Current element ke pehle wale elements locate karta hai.

//input[@id='password']/preceding::label

➡️ Password input se pehle jo label hai usko locate karega.

Interview Me Short Answer

Agar interviewer puche to aise bolo:

XPath axes are used to navigate through elements in the DOM relative to the current node. Common XPath axes include parent, child, ancestor, following, preceding, and sibling axes.

💡 Interview Tip:
Automation me sabse zyada use hone wale axes:

parent

ancestor

following-sibling

Ye dynamic elements locate karne me bahut useful hote hain.
